      <h2>Eligibility for Travel Credit Cards</h2>
      <p>Travel cards are typically mid-to-premium tier products. Here are the common requirements:</p>

      <ul class="feature-list">
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Age:</strong> 21-60 years (salaried) or 21-65 years (self-employed); some premium cards require 25+</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Income:</strong> ₹50,000/month for mid-tier; ₹1,00,000+/month for super-premium travel cards</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Credit Score:</strong> 730+ CIBIL score for most travel cards; 750+ for invitation-only cards like HDFC Infinia</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Valid Passport:</strong> Required for international travel benefits and lounge access activation</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Employment:</strong> Stable salaried employment or established business/professional practice</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Documents:</strong> PAN, Aadhaar, passport, latest 3-month salary slips or 2-year ITR, 6-month bank statement</li>
      </ul>

